<subSubSection id="FBF16577FFE4FFDFFF7D29F7F455FCC5" pageId="19" pageNumber="308" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B35436FCFFE4FFDFFF7D29F7F455FCC5" blockId="19.[151,760,1769,2081]" lastBlockId="19.[828,1437,190,1365]" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFE4FFDFFF7D29F7F01FF8D1" bold="true" box="[151,270,1769,1793]" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Antennae black (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE4FFDFFE3C29F4F35EF8D1" box="[470,591,1770,1793]" captionStart="Figs 4" captionStartId="5.[150,187,2036,2055]" captionTargetBox="[247,1334,221,1972]" captionTargetId="figure-16@5.[179,1408,189,1996]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 4A–F. Dorsal and ventral surface.A–B – Hypoxys immaculatus sp. nov.; C–D – Hypoxys nigroantennatus sp. nov.; E–F – Hypoxys santarensis sp. nov. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177535" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177535/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">Figs 4C,D</figureCitation>
). Antennomere II longer than III. Apex of mandibular plates with black stripe (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE4FFDFFF0B2834F045F891" box="[225,340,1834,1857]" captionStart="Figs 4" captionStartId="5.[150,187,2036,2055]" captionTargetBox="[247,1334,221,1972]" captionTargetId="figure-16@5.[179,1408,189,1996]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 4A–F. Dorsal and ventral surface.A–B – Hypoxys immaculatus sp. nov.; C–D – Hypoxys nigroantennatus sp. nov.; E–F – Hypoxys santarensis sp. nov. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177535" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177535/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">Figs 4C,D</figureCitation>
). Pronotum with smoky stripe reaching posterior margin. Thoracic and abdominal pleurites and sternites with black spots (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE4FFDFFE5D2874F308F851" box="[439,537,1898,1921]" captionStart="Figs 16" captionStartId="21.[151,188,2036,2055]" captionTargetBox="[176,1411,203,1987]" captionTargetId="figure-16@21.[175,1411,189,2007]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 16A–F. Hypoxys nigroantennatus sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177557/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">Figs 16F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE4FFDFFDCF2874F35BF851" box="[549,586,1898,1921]" captionStart="Figs 4" captionStartId="5.[150,187,2036,2055]" captionTargetBox="[247,1334,221,1972]" captionTargetId="figure-16@5.[179,1408,189,1996]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 4A–F. Dorsal and ventral surface.A–B – Hypoxys immaculatus sp. nov.; C–D – Hypoxys nigroantennatus sp. nov.; E–F – Hypoxys santarensis sp. nov. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177535" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177535/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">4D</figureCitation>
). Anterior excavation of metasternal process harboring fourth, third and part of second rostral segment (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE4FFDFFE0928B4F350F811" box="[483,577,1962,1985]" captionStart="Figs 16" captionStartId="21.[151,188,2036,2055]" captionTargetBox="[176,1411,203,1987]" captionTargetId="figure-16@21.[175,1411,189,2007]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 16A–F. Hypoxys nigroantennatus sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177557/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">Fig. 16F</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFE4FFDFFDB928B7F3E9F811" bold="true" box="[595,760,1961,1985]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygophore (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE4FFDFFEFF28D4F08BF831" box="[277,410,1994,2017]" captionStart="Figs 16" captionStartId="21.[151,188,2036,2055]" captionTargetBox="[176,1411,203,1987]" captionTargetId="figure-16@21.[175,1411,189,2007]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 16A–F. Hypoxys nigroantennatus sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177557/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">Figs 16A–D</figureCitation>
). Posterolateral angles developed, straight, acuminate (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE4FFDFFE9828F4F0C7F7D1" box="[370,470,2026,2049]" captionStart="Figs 16" captionStartId="21.[151,188,2036,2055]" captionTargetBox="[176,1411,203,1987]" captionTargetId="figure-16@21.[175,1411,189,2007]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 16A–F. Hypoxys nigroantennatus sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177557/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">Fig. 16A</figureCitation>
). Superior process of genital cup parallel to dorsal rim, elongated, almost reaching posterolateral angles, concave medially; inner (proximal) part truncate, ventral angle with large dentiform process; outer (distal) part tongue-like and enlarged (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE4FFDFFAFB2FE0F481FEC5" box="[1297,1424,254,277]" captionStart="Figs 16" captionStartId="21.[151,188,2036,2055]" captionTargetBox="[176,1411,203,1987]" captionTargetId="figure-16@21.[175,1411,189,2007]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 16A–F. Hypoxys nigroantennatus sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177557/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">Figs 16C,D</figureCitation>
). Paramere with two lobes; anterior lobe square, large, and directed to base of proctiger; lateral lobe large and rounded (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE4FFDFFC9A2E40F2FEFEA5" box="[880,1007,350,373]" captionStart="Figs 16" captionStartId="21.[151,188,2036,2055]" captionTargetBox="[176,1411,203,1987]" captionTargetId="figure-16@21.[175,1411,189,2007]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 16A–F. Hypoxys nigroantennatus sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177557/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">Figs 16C,D</figureCitation>
). Proctiger with posterior face triangular (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE4FFDFFCA92E60F2D8FE45" box="[835,969,382,405]" captionStart="Figs 16" captionStartId="21.[151,188,2036,2055]" captionTargetBox="[176,1411,203,1987]" captionTargetId="figure-16@21.[175,1411,189,2007]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 16A–F. Hypoxys nigroantennatus sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177557/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">Figs 16C,D</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim with expansions developed, distally acuminate, ventrolateral side with broad striated excavation, dorsal side with light brown spot; clearly surpassing level of posterolateral angles (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE4FFDFFAE62EC0F49EFE25" box="[1292,1423,478,501]" captionStart="Figs 16" captionStartId="21.[151,188,2036,2055]" captionTargetBox="[176,1411,203,1987]" captionTargetId="figure-16@21.[175,1411,189,2007]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 16A–F. Hypoxys nigroantennatus sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177557/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">Figs 16B,C</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFE4FFDFFCD62EE3F2EEFDC5" bold="true" box="[828,1023,509,533]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Genital plates (
<figureCitation id="2BD02A79FFE4FFDFFB442EE0F400FDC5" box="[1198,1297,510,533]" captionStart="Figs 16" captionStartId="21.[151,188,2036,2055]" captionTargetBox="[176,1411,203,1987]" captionTargetId="figure-16@21.[175,1411,189,2007]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 16A–F. Hypoxys nigroantennatus sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – genital plates; F – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177557/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">Fig. 16E</figureCitation>
). Valvifers 8 posterior margin with posterolateral angles dentiform and posteriorly directed, inner angle not visible; imaginary line tangent to posterolateral angles not reaching distal margin of valvifers 9; excavation V-shaped. Valvulae 8 visible. Apices of laterotergites 8 clearly above level of apices of abdominal segment VII. Laterotergites 9 surpassing band connecting laterotergites 8; apices slightly below imaginary line tangent to apices of abdominal segment VII.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
