<subSubSection id="FBF16577FFE4FFDFFCD62CC3F5BBFB45" pageId="19" pageNumber="308" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B35436FCFFE4FFDFFCD62CC3F5BBFB45" blockId="19.[828,1437,190,1365]" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFE4FFDFFCD62CC3F523FC25" bold="true" box="[828,1074,989,1013]" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="74EB4D7FFFE4FFDFFBDD2CC0F457FC25" authority="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes, 2021" authorityName="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2021" box="[1079,1350,990,1013]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigroantennatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFE4FFDFFBDD2CC0F457FC25" box="[1079,1350,990,1013]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">Hypoxys nigroantennatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9AAC5795FFE4FFDFFAA62CC0F48CFC25" box="[1356,1437,990,1013]" pageId="19" pageNumber="308" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from the other species of the 
<taxonomicName id="74EB4D7FFFE4FFDFFB2E2CE0F459FBC5" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[1220,1352,1022,1045]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balteatus">
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFE4FFDFFB2E2CE0F459FBC5" box="[1220,1352,1022,1045]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">H. balteatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group because the antennae and margin of the mandibular plates are black; valvifers 8 excavation is also unique in the group. Also see differential diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName id="74EB4D7FFFE4FFDFFACB2B40F28AFB45" authority="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes, 2021" authorityName="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hyalinofasciatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFE4FFDFFACB2B40F28AFB45" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">H. hyalinofasciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9AAC5795FFE4FFDFFC4B2B60F2E5FB45" box="[929,1012,1150,1173]" pageId="19" pageNumber="308" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
for more details.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FBF16577FFE4FFDFFCD62B80F2B2FB25" pageId="19" pageNumber="308" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="B35436FCFFE4FFDFFCD62B80F2B2FB25" blockId="19.[828,1437,190,1365]" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFE4FFDFFCD62B80F2ADFB66" bold="true" box="[828,956,1182,1206]" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named for the black coloration of the antennae (Latin 
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFE4FFDFFC442BA0F2F7FB05" box="[942,998,1214,1237]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">niger</emphasis>
= black, 
<emphasis id="819FEAEEFFE4FFDFFBAD2BA0F5ADFB05" box="[1095,1212,1214,1237]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="308">antennatus</emphasis>
= bearing antennae); adjective.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
